parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult or impossible to turn, increasing the risk of a crash or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The power steering assist light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the steering wheel wobbles or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to control
and warning messages such as "Steering Assist Malfunction" or "Power Steering Fault" appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose steering wheel can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash or accident.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering wheel can be moved from side to side or up and down on the column
and the driver may experience difficulty controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to become difficult or impossible to turn, increasing the risk of a crash or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the steering wheel wobbles or shakes
and warning messages such as "Steering Assist Malfunction" or "Power Steering Fault" appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or shakes when accelerating
the transmission slips or jerks when shifting
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission fluid leaks
the gear shifter becomes stuck
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly when in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to experience difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Flywheel failure can cause the vehicle to experience difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The flywheel is cracked
the vehicle experiences difficulty shifting gears.

coolant leaks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and stalling can cause loss of power, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
difficulty accelerating

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and powertrain issues can cause loss of power, stalling, and difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause injuries or fatalities, especially if the driver is unable to exit the vehicle quickly.
